overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a Sleep Questionnaire
  application by integrating a database, an admin dashboard, and an
  authentication system. The assistant evaluated the existing codebase,
  identified gaps, and proposed a detailed plan. This plan included updating
  demographic data fields, designing a Prisma schema for questionnaire
  responses, developing API endpoints for data submission and retrieval
  (including CSV export), and building a simple admin dashboard. A key decision
  involved implementing a lightweight authentication system. Initially, a custom
  session management approach was taken, but following user feedback, it was
  refactored to leverage Next.js middleware for simpler and more efficient route
  protection. After implementation, thorough testing confirmed that all new
  features—database integration, API functionality, authentication, and the
  admin dashboard—were fully operational, ready for deployment with NeonDB.
